reviews.reviewText: It's important to note that 100 of the pieces are zip ties, so you really have 92 pieces to work with. There is a nice selection of items. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great cable management system
reviews.reviewText: The 192 piece cable management system is a great solution for anyone looking to organize their cables and wires in a neat and discreet manner. One of the standout features of this system is its ability to stick well to various surfaces. Whether you're mounting it on a desk, wall, or even the underside of a table, the adhesive backing holds strong and keeps your cables securely in place.Another great feature of this cable management system is the sheer number of pieces that come included. With 192 pieces, you'll have more than enough to tackle even the most complex cable setups, such as those found in a flight simulator. The assortment of different sizes and shapes ensures that you'll have the perfect piece for every cable, regardless of thickness or length.Once you've installed the system, you'll be amazed at how much more organized and streamlined your setup looks. The cables are neatly bundled together and routed in a way that is both aesthetically pleasing and functional. No more tangled messes or tripping hazards!Overall, I would highly recommend the 192 piece cable management system to anyone looking to declutter their workspace or home entertainment setup. The strong adhesive, abundance of pieces, and sleek design make it a top-notch choice for cable management.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Good assortment of organizers, weak adhesive
reviews.reviewText: I was really impressed by the assortment of options this kit came with. Unfortunately, the adhesive on the batch that I received was less than stellar. I used the Velcro cable straps to secure a monitor power cable and HDMI cable to the bottom of a desk, polyurethane finished butcher board. Unfortunately, within 4 days both straps had fallen off. The other holders on the side and back of the desk are holding ok for now. The ones on top are fine, but people generally buy kits like this to secure cables out of view. So while it’s a good assortment of options, temper your expectations because the adhesive won’t last where you most need it to.It may be that the adhesive on my set is stale or old, or that it simply doesn’t work on my particular surface.
El producto es muy aceptable en calidad y cumple su proposito

reviews.reviewTitle: Adhesive on wire splitters is poor--all other items are good quality
reviews.reviewText: Overall great amount of items for the price, however, the whire splitters have poor adhesion. I luckily only needed a couple, so I've been replacing them as they wear out--however, they won't last more than a week or two before the adhesive is gone.

reviews.reviewTitle: Muy buen kit para organizar la pc o lo que necesites que lleve cables!
reviews.reviewText: Por el precio de 400+ aprox es una muy buena opción por las 192 piezas que trae, en mi set up me sobraron bastantes.. pero las guardare para el siguiente set up que haga o cuando algun familiar necesite reorganizar sus cables etc

Compré este kit para mejorar el manejo de cables que actualmente tengo con mis equipos de computo y ha Sido muy útil, ahora puedo organizar los cables de mis PCS y laptop de modo que no sean visibles y no estorben en mi escritorio.

La verdad esta muy bueno este Kit, el contenido se ajusta muy bien a lo que se necesita para organizar tus cables en el escritorio, es muy versátil y amplia tus opciónes de acomodo, por ejemplo trae una cintas de velcro con adecivo qué yo use para pegarlas debajo del escritorio para sujetar algunos cables de bocinas y un hub usb.En mi caso me sobraron muchas cosas, yo diría que alcanza para organizar dos escritorios o hasta tres si no despercidias nada.
